# Basic

top

# Once the top report comes up there are numerous commands you can use to get more precise information.

# Sort output

SHIFT+O --> field letter

# 'a' sorts by PID, 'e' by username, 'K' by CPU usage, 'n' by memory usage, etc. etc.

# z - highlight process

# c - display absolute path of process

# k - kill process

# SHIFT+W - save top report to /root/.toprc

# You can display processes by user as follows:

top -u username
